verbose_text: Notably, NKp44 expression allows to discriminate two ILC3 subsets characterized by unique cytokine patterns : NKp44 + ILC3 are able to produce IL-22 and are dependent on the Aryl Hydrocarbon Receptor, whereas human LTi and NKp44 neg ILC3 produce IL-17A.
evidence: LTi and NKp44 neg  ILC3 produce IL-17A
